      • LOWER_BOUND

        static final String LOWER_BOUND
        The lower bound on the number of rounds to run. Can be zero (0) or one (1). A lower bound of zero is a special kind of path - the Zero Length Path. A zero length path connects a vertex to itself (in graph parlance). In the context of arbitrary length paths it means we bind the input onto the output regardless of whether they are actually connected via the path or not.

      • MIDDLE_TERM

        static final String MIDDLE_TERM

      • EDGE_VAR

        static final String EDGE_VAR
        The edge variable. This is an extension that allows the caller to understand how a node was visited (what was the edge that led to it). If set, this will allow in duplicate solutions in violation of the SPARQL spec (if a node can be reached by more than one path there will be one solution emitted per path). Used in conjunction with the middle term. If the middle term is a var, the edge var must not be the same var, since the middle var is used to calculate transitive closure.

      • DROP_VARS

        static final String DROP_VARS
        A list of intermediate variables (IVariables) used by the ALP op that should be dropped from the solutions after each round.
